title._content: Monument to the First Meeting House, Keene NH

description._content: TITLE Monument to the First Meeting House, Keene NH CREATOR SUBJECT Monuments & memorials - NH - Keene DESCRIPTION Photograph of the Monument to the First Meeting House, erected in 1913 in Keene New Hampshire. It reads "The first meeting house in Upper Ashuelot now Keene was built on this knoll in 1736-7. Here also was located the burying ground of the original settlers. Erected by Ashuelot Chapter, Daughters of the American Revolution in 1913." PUBLISHER Keene Public Library DATE DIGITAL 20080321 DATE ORIGINAL RESOURCE TYPE photographs FORMAT image/jpg RESOURCE IDENTIFIER hsykmsc007 RIGHTS MANAGMENT No known restriction on publication.
